# Queue (FIFO – First In First Out)
# Operations:
# enqueue(x) → add to the rear
# dequeue() → remove from the front
# Behavior: First element added is the first one removed.
# Example in real life: People standing in a queue at a ticket counter.

# ✅ Important Note:
# ADT is about what the data can do (operations), while data structure is how it actually does it (implementation).
# ADT = Conceptual
# Data Structure = Physical implementation